  <prompt>
    Author the architecture doc + maker guide for the Playbook-driven LLM Output pattern that
    Wave 11 finalizes. These docs are NOT optional — operator made them a binding requirement
    so Insights Engine, future Workspace narrative outputs, work assignment briefings, project
    status updates, document review summaries (and many other future consumers) can be authored
    without rediscovering the design. Each doc reflects WHAT WAS SHIPPED in T111, not what was
    originally designed — read the T111 final code state before writing.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE technical writer + AI platform architect. Audience: future devs authoring new
    narrative-output consumers (Workspace UX features) + makers authoring playbook + Action JPS.
    Goal: produce docs concise enough to actually be read (target: each doc &lt;400 lines), specific
    enough to copy from.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Three deliverables:
    1. `docs/architecture/SPAARKE-PLAYBOOK-LLM-OUTPUT-PATTERN.md` — authoritative architecture
       reference covering the two-layer design (Layer 1 orchestrator template resolution + Layer 2
       PromptSchemaRenderer "## Input" section), runtime data flow, component model, file map,
       and what's centralized vs what's per-consumer.
    2. `docs/guides/BUILD-A-NEW-NARRATIVE-OUTPUT-CONSUMER.md` — step-by-step maker tutorial with
       two worked examples (Daily Briefing as the shipped reference, Insight Engine Matter Summary
       as a future example) covering: trigger / playbook composition / Action JPS authoring / output
       destination wiring / testing / deployment.
    3. Update root `CLAUDE.md` §17 pointer table with row pointing to the new architecture doc
       (load-bearing for future agents).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="design-source">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/wave11-orchestrator-resolution-design.md</file>
    <file purpose="t111-implementation">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookTemplateContextBuilder.cs (created by T111)</file>
