  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-08">No SUPERSEDED markers, no redirect stubs. Cross-link to existing docs that are still accurate. If existing AI-ARCHITECTURE.md / ai-architecture-actions-nodes-scopes.md needs minor updates (cross-reference back to the new pattern doc), do it inline — don't create archive copies.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §17">New architecture doc gets a pointer-table row in root CLAUDE.md §17. Doc title format matches existing convention.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">Reuse-first: confirm the new docs do NOT duplicate AI-ARCHITECTURE.md or ai-architecture-playbook-runtime.md scope. They're focused specifically on the narrative-output pattern.</constraint>
    <constraint source="audience">Architecture doc audience = future devs. Maker guide audience = playbook + Action JPS authors. Don't mix them in one doc.</constraint>
    <constraint source="length-discipline">Each doc target: &lt;400 lines. Use tables, code blocks, diagrams. Concise wins.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ship-reality">Docs reflect SHIPPED code (read T111 final state). If T111 design deviated from the spike doc, document what shipped — not what was planned.</constraint>
  </constraints>

